    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "DAOs have struggled with legal ambiguity, resource allocation inefficiencies, and broken incentive structures. Scalable Network Organizations (SNOs) emerge as the next evolutionary step, combining the principles of decentralization with the operational rigor of traditional organizations. SNOs provide a structured framework for decentralized governance, sustainable operations, and global scalability -- delivering on the original promise of DAOs while enabling organizations to scale.",
